---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = 'Patient Privacy | Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS - Manteca Dentist';
const description = 'Patient privacy rights and how your health information is protected at Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS in Manteca, CA.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Patient Privacy</h1>
    <p>Your privacy is our priority. Learn how we protect your personal health information.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Our Commitment to Your Privacy</h2>
    <p>At the dental practice of Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS, we are committed to protecting the privacy of our patients. We understand that your personal health information is sensitive, and we take our responsibility to safeguard it seriously.</p>

    <h2>How We Protect Your Information</h2>
    <p>We maintain physical, administrative, and technical safeguards that comply with federal and state regulations to protect your personal health information. Our staff is trained in privacy practices and understands the importance of maintaining confidentiality.</p>

    <h2>How We May Use Your Health Information</h2>

    <h3>Treatment</h3>
    <p>We use your health information to provide you with dental treatment and services. We may share information with other healthcare providers involved in your care.</p>

    <h3>Payment</h3>
    <p>We may use and disclose your health information to obtain payment for the services we provide. This may include sharing information with your insurance company for claims processing.</p>

    <h3>Healthcare Operations</h3>
    <p>We may use your health information for practice operations such as quality assessment, staff training, and compliance activities.</p>

    <h2>When We May Disclose Your Information Without Your Authorization</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>As required by law:</strong> When disclosure is required by federal, state, or local law</li>
      <li><strong>Public health purposes:</strong> For public health activities such as disease reporting</li>
      <li><strong>Health oversight:</strong> To health oversight agencies for audits and investigations</li>
      <li><strong>Judicial proceedings:</strong> In response to court orders or lawful subpoenas</li>
      <li><strong>Law enforcement:</strong> For law enforcement purposes as required by law</li>
      <li><strong>Serious threat:</strong> To prevent a serious threat to health or safety</li>
      <li><strong>Family members:</strong> To family members or others involved in your care, when appropriate</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the following rights regarding your health information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Right to access:</strong> You may request to see and obtain copies of your health records</li>
      <li><strong>Right to amend:</strong> You may request corrections to your health information if you believe it is inaccurate</li>
      <li><strong>Right to restrict:</strong> You may request restrictions on certain uses and disclosures of your information</li>
      <li><strong>Right to confidential communications:</strong> You may request that we communicate with you in a specific manner or at a specific location</li>
      <li><strong>Right to an accounting:</strong> You may request a list of certain disclosures of your health information</li>
      <li><strong>Right to a paper copy:</strong> You may request a paper copy of this notice at any time</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes to This Notice</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to change the terms of this notice at any time. We will post the current notice in our office and make it available on our website. The notice will always contain the effective date.</p>

    <h2>Complaints</h2>
    <p>If you believe your privacy rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with our office or with the Office for Civil Rights, U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. We will not retaliate against you for filing a complaint.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>For questions about our privacy practices or to exercise your privacy rights, please contact:</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS</strong><br />
      715 N Main St<br />
      Manteca, CA 95336<br />
      Phone: <a href="tel:+12092392990">(209) 239-2990</a>
    </p>

    <p>For the full HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices, please visit our <a href="/hipaa-privacy-notice/">HIPAA Privacy Notice</a> page.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>